research in

25:14.980 --> 25:18.317 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
the middle of an epidemic.

25:18.350 --> 25:24.690 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: In Freetown,
pharmacist Morrison
Jusu is among those who
scrambled to get this

25:24.723 --> 25:29.862 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
trial under way at all. He is
anxious to know
if the hard work will pay off.

25:29.895 --> 25:35.267 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MORRISON JUSU: We are really
looking forward
to it being successful, so that
someday in

25:35.300 --> 25:40.105 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the future, we will be able to
say, yes, I
was a part of that team and I
contributed.

25:40.139 --> 25:43.742 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
So, it will be a great feeling
then.

25:43.776 --> 25:51.917 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
MILES O'BRIEN: The answer will
have to wait,
but no one doubts the vaccine
will meet its

25:51.950 --> 25:55.621 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
viral foe someday.

25:55.654 --> 26:05.597 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Miles O'Brien, the "PBS
NewsHour," Freetown,
Sierra Leone.

26:05.631 --> 26:15.674 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Before the president
and Congress
left town for the holidays, they
managed to

26:15.674 --> 26:23.282 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
GWEN IFILL: Before the president
and Congress
left town for the holidays, they
managed to

26:23.315 --> 26:30.222 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
enact a massive 2,000-page
package of spending
and tax cuts. Typically, these
laws draw attention

26:30.255 --> 26:33.659 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
only for the chaos they create,
like shutting
down the government.

26:33.692 --> 26:38.363 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
But there's a lot more deep
inside, in this
case, a significant and
controversial new

26:38.397 --> 26:44.736 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
law governing cyber-security and
Internet
data. The new law encourages
private companies

26:44.770 --> 26:50.576 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to share data about cyber-hacks
with the government.
It protects companies from
liability, and

26:50.609 --> 26:56.248 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
it also allows data to shared
with other companies
and with the Department of
Homeland Security.

26:56.281 --> 26:59.451 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Lawmakers from both parties said
it was a
good deal.

26:59.485 --> 27:04.456 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
SEN. DIANNE FEINSTEIN (D),
California: If
someone sees a particular virus
or harmful

27:04.490 --> 27:10.062 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
cyber-signature, they should
tell others,
so they can protect themselves.
That's what

27:10.095 --> 27:11.930 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
this bill does.

27:11.964 --> 27:15.234 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
REP. DEVIN NUNES (R),
California: We believe
that sharing is an area where
you really can't

27:15.267 --> 27:19.004 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
do any harm. It doesn't hurt
