with the
government.

30:13.512 --> 30:16.148 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But you say
coerced. Isn't
this voluntary?

30:16.181 --> 30:20.385 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELISSA SHEVINSKY: They say that
it's voluntary,
but if the government comes to
you and says

30:20.419 --> 30:24.189 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
that they want information, it's
tricky to
stand up and say no.

30:24.222 --> 30:26.558 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, Jim Lewis,
what do you
see about that?

30:26.591 --> 30:31.563 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES LEWIS: This is DHS we're
talking about.
And it's very hard for them to
coerce anyone.

30:31.596 --> 30:33.665 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
So, it's voluntary.

30:33.699 --> 30:38.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That's actually my concern, is,
since it's
voluntary, people are unlikely
to do anything.

30:38.970 --> 30:43.675 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
This doesn't expand the
information that companies
are gathering. It's their
decision whether

30:43.709 --> 30:48.480 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
or not they share it, and
there's no authority
in the bill for the government
to coerce anyone.

30:48.513 --> 30:51.183 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, I hadn't even thought about
coercion as
a problem.

30:51.216 --> 30:52.718 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What would you
like to see
happen?

30:52.751 --> 30:54.786 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JAMES LEWIS: We're going to have
to tackle
some hard issues.

30:54.820 --> 30:58.957 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
We're going to have to tackle
what is the
role of the military, where do
we need to

30:58.990 --> 31:05.797 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
regulate, and how do we work
with other countries
to come to some understanding on
what we should

31:05.831 --> 31:07.299 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
or shouldn't do in cyberspace.

31:07.332 --> 31:10.102 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What do you see
the government
saying to companies here?

31:10.135 --> 31:15.440 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES LEWIS: What they're saying
is, you either
know than we do, which could be
true. You

31:15.474 --> 31:20.445 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
certainly know different things
than we do.
And so if you can give us that
threat information,

31:20.479 --> 31:23.381 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and we can share back with you,
it will help
everyone.

31:23.415 --> 31:26.852 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
It could work. I mean, it hasn't
worked so
far, but that's the theory.

31:26.885 --> 31:31.189 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, Elissa
Shevinsky, where
do you see this line, from where
you sit,

31:31.223 --> 31:33.125 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this line of security and
privacy?

31:33.158 --> 31:39.064 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELISSA SHEVINSKY: We need to
actually build
and enforce real security. That
requires encrypting

31:39.097 --> 31:40.966 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
our data.

31:40.999 --> 31:46.905 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It requires taking new measures
in the government.
So many government offices were
hacked this

31:46.938 --> 31:51.476 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
last year. We need to review
their security
practices if they are going to
be holding

31:51.510 --> 31:53.311 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
more citizen data.

31:53.345 --> 31:57.582 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Well, that could
be right.
This is a very evolving threat,
right, both

31:57.616 --> 31:59.518 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
to the private sector and
government.

31:59.551 --> 32:03.021 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ELISSA SHEVINSKY: That's right.
And this bill
doesn't address that.

32:03.054 --> 32:08.960 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
This bill is information
gathering for DHS.
And it doesn't actually support
what we need

32:08.994 --> 32:13.098 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
to improve the security of our
companies and
to improve the security of our
government

32:13.131 --> 32:14.900 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
agencies.

32:14.933 --> 32:16.968 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: What would you
like to see?
What kind of system would you
like to see

32:17.002 --> 32:18.837 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
in place?

32:18.870 --> 32:22.808 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
ELISSA SHEVINSKY: We need to
actually improve
the security of how we're
storing and managing

32:22.841 --> 32:28.747 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
data, who has access to that
data. More threat
intelligence won't help us,
because we already

32:28.780 --> 32:30.515 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
know what the threats look like.

32:30.549 --> 32:33.652 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Jim Lewis, is it
correct that
there is still a lot to work
out? There's

32:33.685 --> 32:35.687 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
still a lot we don't know about
how this is
going to be implemented.

32:35.720 --> 32:41.159 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JAMES LEWIS: Yes. The bill has a
lot of reporting
dates and actions for
implementation.

32:41.193 --> 32:48.767 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
I think that, you know, the
debate over the
-- between the privacy community
and the agencies

32:48.800 --> 32:54.539 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
was, where does the information
go? They settled
on DHS. And now DHS has to
prepare itself.

32:54.573 --> 32:59.211 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
So, there is a lot of action
here. Right now,
this doesn't change anything.
Maybe three

32:59.244 --> 33:02.180 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
months from now, we will see
some improvement.

33:02.214 --> 33:07.085 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: How would you
judge success
